{# site/templates/pages/p3-hirefire.html.j2 #}
{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% set ag = card_data.aggregate %}
{% set sc = card_data.scorecard %}
{% set names = card_data.meta.names %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/pages/p3.css">
{% endblock %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="p3-intro">
  <p class="p3-headline">
    Goyal&ndash;Wahal (2008): plan sponsors hire after strong trailing performance and
    fire after weak &mdash; yet the <strong>fired managers go on to match or beat the
    newly hired ones</strong>. The round-trip adds nothing; the timing is the mistake.
    This exhibit audits <strong>the allocator's own decision</strong>, not the manager's skill.
    This is a fully <span class="p3-synthetic">synthetic</span> decision history of
    {{ ag.n_events }} events over {{ card_data.meta.n_managers }} managers.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="p3-panel p3-panel--primary">
  <h2 class="p3-panel__title">Process value-add &mdash; shrunk toward the base rate</h2>
  {% if ag.raw_mean_gated %}
  <div class="power-gate" role="note">
    <span class="power-gate__title">Raw average refused</span>
    <p class="power-gate__reason">
      {{ ag.gate_banner }} Effective N is
      {{ "%.1f"|format(ag.n_effective) }} ({{ ag.n_events }} events across
      {{ ag.n_cohorts }} quarterly cohorts, design effect
      {{ "%.2f"|format(ag.design_effect) }}) &mdash; below the
      {{ card_data.meta.min_events }}-event gate.
    </p>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="valueadd" data-zero="0"
       data-lo="{{ ag.posterior.ci_lo }}"
       data-point="{{ ag.posterior.point }}"
       data-hi="{{ ag.posterior.ci_hi }}">
    <span class="interval-stat__label">Posterior process value-add (annualized round-trip)</span>
    <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%+.1f"|format(ag.posterior.point * 100) }}%</span>
    <div class="interval-stat__rail">
      <div class="interval-stat__band"></div>
      <div class="interval-stat__zero"></div>
      <div class="interval-stat__point"></div>
    </div>
    <span class="interval-stat__range">90% interval
      {{ "%+.1f"|format(ag.posterior.ci_lo * 100) }}% &hellip;
      {{ "%+.1f"|format(ag.posterior.ci_hi * 100) }}%</span>
  </div>

  <p class="p3-verdict">
    <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="noise">{{ ag.verdict_chip }}</span>
    <span class="p3-verdict__note">
      The prior is pinned at the Goyal&ndash;Wahal null (0), prior scale
      {{ "%.0f"|format(card_data.meta.prior_scale * 100) }}%/yr. The interval
      straddles zero &mdash; not a failure to conclude, it is the conclusion.
    </span>
  </p>

  <p class="p3-detect">
    {% if ag.events_to_detect.n %}
    At a true {{ "%.0f"|format(ag.events_to_detect.true_gap * 100) }}%/yr edge and
    &rho; = {{ "%.2f"|format(ag.events_to_detect.rho) }}, the posterior interval would
    first exclude zero at &asymp; <strong>{{ ag.events_to_detect.n | int }} decisions</strong>
    &mdash; more than a career of governance holds.
    {% else %}
    At this cohort correlation, <strong>no attainable decision count</strong> reaches
    significance &mdash; the value is prospective calibration, not a p-value.
    {% endif %}
  </p>
</section>

<section class="p3-explainer" aria-label="What this exhibit shows">
  <h2 class="p3-panel__title">What this exhibit shows</h2>
  <div class="p3-explainer__block">
    <h3 class="p3-explainer__sub">What you are looking at</h3>
    <p class="p3-note">
      The interval above estimates whether the allocator's decisions added value after
      shrinking a small, correlated history toward a zero base rate. It crosses zero,
      so the honest answer is that this history does not distinguish the process from
      the base rate.
    </p>
    <p class="p3-note">
      The synthetic generator is deliberately built to reproduce the published stylized fact. It
      tests ledger, counterfactual, shrinkage, and refusal mechanics; it does not independently validate
      the paper or any real committee's skill.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="p3-explainer__block">
    <h3 class="p3-explainer__sub">How to read it</h3>
    <ul class="p3-explainer__list">
      <li><strong>Interval first:</strong> width is uncertainty; crossing zero is the
        conclusion, not a missing result.</li>
      <li><strong>Cohort path next:</strong> compare fired managers with the
        replacements that received their capital.</li>
      <li><strong>Scorecard:</strong> grade one decision against the thesis and kill
        criterion written before the outcome.</li>
      <li><strong>Decision histories:</strong> open the final disclosure only when the
        individual cases are useful.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="p3-note"><a href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}specs/{{ card.id }}.html">Read the full article</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="p3-panel">
  <h2 class="p3-panel__title">Counterfactual cohort &mdash; fired vs replacement, forward</h2>
  <p class="p3-note">
    Event-time forward path of the <strong>fired</strong> managers against the
    <strong>replacements</strong> that funded their mandates. The fired recover; the
    replacements fade &mdash; mean reversion, exactly the round-trip Goyal&ndash;Wahal
    found. This is calibration of the termination bar, not an accusation.
  </p>
  <div class="p3-cohort__frame">
    <span class="p3-cohort__y-label">Forward cumulative relative return (%)</span>
    <svg class="p3-cohort" viewBox="0 0 100 40" preserveAspectRatio="none"
         role="img" aria-label="Fired vs replacement forward paths"></svg>
    <div class="p3-cohort__x-axis"><span>Decision</span><span>Months after decision</span><span>36</span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="p3-cohort__legend">
    <span class="p3-legend p3-legend--fired">Fired managers at end <strong>{{ "%+.1f"|format((card_data.cohort_paths.fired | last) * 100) }}%</strong></span>
    <span class="p3-legend p3-legend--replacement">Replacement managers at end <strong>{{ "%+.1f"|format((card_data.cohort_paths.replacement | last) * 100) }}%</strong></span>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="p3-panel">
  <h2 class="p3-panel__title">Journal scorecard &mdash; decision graded against its pre-commitments</h2>
  <div class="p3-scorecard">
    <div class="p3-scorecard__head">
      <span class="p3-scorecard__name">{{ names[sc.manager_id] }}</span>
      <span class="ledger-row__meta">{{ sc.decision_type }} &middot; {{ sc.decision_date }}
        &middot; {{ sc.horizon_years }}y horizon</span>
    </div>
    <dl class="p3-scorecard__grid">
      <dt>Thesis (pre-committed)</dt><dd>{{ sc.thesis }}</dd>
      <dt>Kill criterion (pre-committed)</dt><dd>{{ sc.kill_criterion }}</dd>
      <dt>Expected alpha</dt><dd>{{ "%+.1f"|format(sc.expected_alpha_annual * 100) }}%/yr</dd>
      <dt>Realized forward ({{ sc.horizon_years }}y)</dt>
        <dd>{{ "%+.1f"|format(sc.realized_forward * 100) }}%</dd>
      <dt>Realized factor alpha</dt>
        <dd>{{ "%+.1f"|format(sc.realized_factor_alpha_annual * 100) }}%/yr</dd>
      <dt>Kill criterion met?</dt>
        <dd>{{ "yes" if sc.kill_criterion_met else "no" }}</dd>
    </dl>
    <p class="p3-scorecard__grade">
      Graded on the bar set <em>before</em> the draw, not on the hindsight outcome
      &mdash; a good decision with a bad draw is not a bad decision.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="p3-panel">
  <h2 class="p3-panel__title">Decision histories</h2>
  <p class="p3-note">
    At this decision count the stories <em>are</em> the honest output; nothing is
    averaged away. Each row is one decision, its counterfactual, and the forward gap.
  </p>
  <details class="p3-event-details">
    <summary>Show all {{ ag.n_events }} individual decisions</summary>
  <div class="p3-ledger">
    {% for ev in card_data.events %}
    <article class="p3-event p3-event--{{ ev.value_verdict }}">
      <div class="p3-event__head">
        <span class="p3-event__type">{{ ev.decision_type }}</span>
        <span class="p3-event__name">{{ names[ev.manager_id] }}</span>
        <span class="ledger-row__meta">{{ ev.decision_date }} &middot;
          {{ ev.counterfactual_rung }} &middot; {{ ev.horizon_years }}y</span>
        <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="{{ 'aligned' if ev.value_verdict == 'helped'
          else 'contradicted' if ev.value_verdict == 'hurt' else 'noise' }}">{{ ev.value_verdict }}</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p3-event__gaps">
        <span>forward gap (raw) <strong>{{ "%+.1f"|format(ev.forward_gap_raw * 100) }}%</strong></span>
        <span>factor-adjusted <strong>{{ "%+.1f"|format(ev.forward_gap_factor_adj * 100) }}%</strong></span>
        <span>kill criterion {{ "met" if ev.kill_criterion_met else "not met" }}</span>
      </div>
      <p class="p3-event__thesis">{{ ev.thesis }}</p>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  </details>
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>Two halves with a hard division of labor. The <strong>journal</strong> is a
prospective discipline instrument &mdash; a schema (thesis, expected alpha, horizon,
kill criterion) filled at the decision moment, before the outcome is known, the only
clean defense against outcome bias. The <strong>ledger</strong> is deterministic
event-time accounting: forward excess returns and factor-adjusted gaps (reusing the
uncertainty-honest factor regression), a counterfactual resolved by a fixed hierarchy
(replacement-paired &rarr; peer-median &rarr; benchmark), and a signed value-add per
event where positive always means the decision helped.</p>
<p>The one crossing-events number is the <strong>process value-add posterior</strong>:
the same normal-normal shrinkage the skill engine uses, with the grand mean pinned at
the Goyal&ndash;Wahal base rate (0). Effective N is honest &mdash; decisions in one
market episode share a forward path, so the cohort block bootstrap and the design
effect deflate the sample far below the event count. The raw average is refused below
the effective-events gate; the posterior renders at any N, and its straddling-zero
interval is the product, not a bug.</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block body_scripts %}
<script src="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/p3-hirefire.js"></script>
{% endblock %}
